# agent-store
- label: agent-store builds a Rust CLI binary named agent-store that exits 0 for --help and prints usage
  id: 28o
  command: sh -c 'cargo run --quiet -- --help > /tmp/agent-store-help-28o.txt && grep -Fq "Usage: agent-store" /tmp/agent-store-help-28o.txt'
  tags: [implemented]
- agent-store keeps command parsing, command behavior, persistence, and output formatting separated behind small internal boundaries @draft

# CLI

## records
- label: agent-store create <kind> key=value... creates a Record, stores <kind> as its queryable kind, stores each key=value Field, and prints the Record ID
  id: b98
  command: sh -c 'set -eu; repo=$PWD; tmp=$(mktemp -d); trap "rm -rf \"$tmp\"" EXIT; cd "$tmp"; CARGO_TARGET_DIR="$repo/target/facts-b98" cargo run --quiet --manifest-path "$repo/Cargo.toml" -- init >/tmp/agent-store-create-b98-init.out; id=$(CARGO_TARGET_DIR="$repo/target/facts-b98" cargo run --quiet --manifest-path "$repo/Cargo.toml" -- create task title=Write status=open); printf "%s\n" "$id" | grep -Eq "^[a-z0-9]{6,8}$"; out=$(CARGO_TARGET_DIR="$repo/target/facts-b98" cargo run --quiet --manifest-path "$repo/Cargo.toml" -- get "$id"); test "$out" = "$id task status=open title=Write"'
  tags: [implemented]
- agent-store find accepts a Query as either one quoted argument or multiple unquoted arguments joined with spaces, then prints matching Records @draft
- agent-store rm <ID> hard-deletes the Record with that short ID and reports whether a record was removed @draft
- label: agent-store get <ID> prints the Record with that short ID in the default record output format
  id: rzr
  command: sh -c 'set -eu; repo=$PWD; tmp=$(mktemp -d); trap "rm -rf \"$tmp\"" EXIT; cd "$tmp"; CARGO_TARGET_DIR="$repo/target/facts-rzr" cargo run --quiet --manifest-path "$repo/Cargo.toml" -- init >/tmp/agent-store-get-rzr-init.out; id=$(CARGO_TARGET_DIR="$repo/target/facts-rzr" cargo run --quiet --manifest-path "$repo/Cargo.toml" -- create decision choice=sqlite area=persistence); out=$(CARGO_TARGET_DIR="$repo/target/facts-rzr" cargo run --quiet --manifest-path "$repo/Cargo.toml" -- get "$id"); test "$out" = "$id decision area=persistence choice=sqlite"'
  tags: [implemented]
- agent-store set <ID> key=value... updates supplied Fields on an existing Record, accepts empty and null values, and leaves unspecified Fields unchanged @draft
- agent-store unset <ID> key... removes the supplied Fields from an existing Record without deleting the Record @draft

## output
- label: agent-store prints Records one per line as <id> <kind> key=value... with stable field ordering and shell-quoted values when needed
  id: zaj
  command: sh -c 'set -eu; repo=$PWD; tmp=$(mktemp -d); trap "rm -rf \"$tmp\"" EXIT; cd "$tmp"; CARGO_TARGET_DIR="$repo/target/facts-zaj" cargo run --quiet --manifest-path "$repo/Cargo.toml" -- init >/tmp/agent-store-output-zaj-init.out; id=$(CARGO_TARGET_DIR="$repo/target/facts-zaj" cargo run --quiet --manifest-path "$repo/Cargo.toml" -- create note title="hello world" status=open empty=); out=$(CARGO_TARGET_DIR="$repo/target/facts-zaj" cargo run --quiet --manifest-path "$repo/Cargo.toml" -- get "$id"); test "$out" = "$id note empty='\'''\'' status=open title='\''hello world'\''"'
  tags: [implemented]
- all commands that emit records, summaries, or mutation results support --json for structured machine-readable output @draft

## init
- label: agent-store init creates .agent-store/ in the current directory and adds a .agent-store/ ignore rule to .gitignore
  id: k6a
  command: sh -c 'set -eu; repo=$PWD; tmp=$(mktemp -d); trap "rm -rf \"$tmp\"" EXIT; cd "$tmp"; CARGO_TARGET_DIR="$repo/target/facts-k6a" cargo run --quiet --manifest-path "$repo/Cargo.toml" -- init >/tmp/agent-store-init-k6a.out; test -d .agent-store; grep -Fxq ".agent-store/" .gitignore'
  tags: [implemented]
- label: agent-store init installs the agent-store, agent-store-patterns, and agent-store-pipelines builtin skills as SKILL.md files under both .agents/skills and .claude/skills
  id: 4je
  command: sh -c "set -eu; repo=\$PWD; tmp=\$(mktemp -d); cd \"\$tmp\"; CARGO_TARGET_DIR=\"\$repo/target/facts-4je\" cargo run --quiet --manifest-path \"\$repo/Cargo.toml\" -- init >/tmp/agent-store-init-4je.out; for root in .agents/skills .claude/skills; do for skill in agent-store agent-store-patterns agent-store-pipelines; do test -f \"\$root/\$skill/SKILL.md\"; grep -Fq \"name: \$skill\" \"\$root/\$skill/SKILL.md\"; done; done; rm -rf \"\$tmp\""
  tags: [implemented]
- label: agent-store init appends a managed usage block to existing AGENTS.md and CLAUDE.md files while preserving their existing content
  id: ciy
  command: sh -c "set -eu; repo=\$PWD; tmp=\$(mktemp -d); cd \"\$tmp\"; printf \"user-authored line\\n\" > AGENTS.md; printf \"user-authored line\\n\" > CLAUDE.md; CARGO_TARGET_DIR=\"\$repo/target/facts-ciy\" cargo run --quiet --manifest-path \"\$repo/Cargo.toml\" -- init >/tmp/agent-store-init-ciy.out; for doc in AGENTS.md CLAUDE.md; do grep -Fq \"user-authored line\" \"\$doc\"; grep -Fq \"<!-- agent-store:start -->\" \"\$doc\"; grep -Fq \"agent-store init\" \"\$doc\"; grep -Fq \"<!-- agent-store:end -->\" \"\$doc\"; done; rm -rf \"\$tmp\""
  tags: [implemented]
- label: agent-store init can be run repeatedly without duplicating managed instruction blocks or overwriting pre-existing skill files
  id: vpz
  command: sh -c "set -eu; repo=\$PWD; tmp=\$(mktemp -d); cd \"\$tmp\"; printf \"user-authored line\\n\" > AGENTS.md; printf \"user-authored line\\n\" > CLAUDE.md; mkdir -p .agents/skills/agent-store .claude/skills/agent-store; printf \"custom agent skill\\n\" > .agents/skills/agent-store/SKILL.md; printf \"custom claude skill\\n\" > .claude/skills/agent-store/SKILL.md; CARGO_TARGET_DIR=\"\$repo/target/facts-vpz\" cargo run --quiet --manifest-path \"\$repo/Cargo.toml\" -- init >/tmp/agent-store-init-vpz-1.out; CARGO_TARGET_DIR=\"\$repo/target/facts-vpz\" cargo run --quiet --manifest-path \"\$repo/Cargo.toml\" -- init >/tmp/agent-store-init-vpz-2.out; test \"\$(grep -Fc \"<!-- agent-store:start -->\" AGENTS.md)\" -eq 1; test \"\$(grep -Fc \"<!-- agent-store:start -->\" CLAUDE.md)\" -eq 1; test \"\$(grep -Fc \".agent-store/\" .gitignore)\" -eq 1; grep -Fxq \"custom agent skill\" .agents/skills/agent-store/SKILL.md; grep -Fxq \"custom claude skill\" .claude/skills/agent-store/SKILL.md; rm -rf \"\$tmp\""
  tags: [implemented]

## aliases
- agent-store cr is a short alias for create with identical arguments, behavior, and output @draft
- agent-store ls is a short alias for find with identical query behavior and output @draft

## hooks
- agent-store hook add <event> [<Query>] -- <bash command> creates a Hook and prints the Hook ID @draft
- agent-store hook ls prints configured Hooks in a compact deterministic format @draft
- agent-store hook rm <ID> deletes the Hook with that short ID and reports whether a hook was removed @draft

## context
- agent-store ctx prints a compact deterministic Quick Context summary without printing individual Records by default @draft
- agent-store context is a readable alias for ctx with identical behavior and output @draft

## links
- agent-store link <from> <rel> <to> creates an idempotent directional Link between two Records @draft
- agent-store unlink <from> <rel> <to> removes a directional Link and succeeds without side effects when the Link is already absent @draft
- agent-store links <ID> prints incoming and outgoing Links for the Record in a compact deterministic format @draft
- agent-store find supports filtering Records by incoming and outgoing Links, relation names, and linked Record IDs in the first link-enabled release @draft

# domain
- label: a Store is a project-local SQLite-backed database under .agent-store
  command: bash tests/facts/store_schema_migrations.sh store_is_project_local
  tags: [implemented]
- a Record is a stored item with a generated 6-8 character random hash ID, a kind, and arbitrary named fields @draft
- a Field is a key-value attribute attached to a Record @draft
- a Query is a boolean expression over Record fields, typed comparisons, parentheses, and link predicates @draft
- a Hook is a stored automation rule that pairs a Store Event, an optional Query condition, and a Bash command @draft
- a Store Event is a successful create, set, unset, rm, link, or unlink operation on stored data @draft
- a Hook Run is a stored execution result for one Hook invocation, including the event, affected Record ID, exit status, and captured output summary @draft
- a Quick Context is a bounded Store summary intended to orient an agent before it chooses specific retrieval commands @draft
- a Link is a directional typed relation from one Record to another Record @draft
- label: one Link table shape represents one-to-one, one-to-many, and many-to-many relations without per-kind schema changes
  command: bash tests/facts/store_schema_migrations.sh record_links_cardinality_shape
  tags: [implemented]

# persistence
- label: SQLite schema changes are applied through migrations when a Store is opened
  command: bash tests/facts/store_schema_migrations.sh migrations_apply_on_open
  tags: [implemented]
- persistence errors preserve enough context for the CLI to print actionable failures without panics @draft
- Record storage supports querying arbitrary Field values without requiring a Rust code change for each new field name @draft

## schema
- label: the initial SQLite schema stores Records, Fields, Links, Store Events, Hooks, Hook Runs, and schema migrations in separate normalized tables
  command: bash tests/facts/store_schema_migrations.sh initial_schema_tables
  tags: [implemented]
- label: the records table stores id, kind, created_at, and updated_at as first-class columns
  command: bash tests/facts/store_schema_migrations.sh records_columns
  tags: [implemented]
- label: the record_fields table stores one row per Field with raw value plus typed columns for text, number, timestamp, boolean, and null-aware comparisons
  command: bash tests/facts/store_schema_migrations.sh record_fields_typed_columns
  tags: [implemented]
- label: the record_links table stores from_record_id, rel, to_record_id, and created_at with a unique key over from_record_id, rel, and to_record_id
  command: bash tests/facts/store_schema_migrations.sh record_links_columns_unique
  tags: [implemented]
- label: deleting a Record cascades to its Fields and Links but does not delete other Records linked to it
  command: bash tests/facts/store_schema_migrations.sh record_delete_cascades_links
  tags: [implemented]
- hard deletes write a Store Event with a pre-delete Record snapshot before removing the active Record row @draft

## migrations
- schema migrations are embedded in the Rust binary and run inside transactions when a Store is opened @implemented
- label: applied migrations are recorded with version, name, checksum, and applied_at, and checksum mismatches stop the command with an actionable error
  command: bash tests/facts/store_schema_migrations.sh migration_checksum_mismatch
  tags: [implemented]

## concurrency
- SQLite connections enable foreign keys, WAL mode, and a busy timeout so multiple concurrent agent-store processes can read and write safely @implemented
- each create, set, unset, rm, link, unlink, hook add, and hook rm command applies its Store mutation in a transaction @draft

# architecture
- the crate exposes a narrow persistence interface so command behavior can be tested without depending on sqlite file layout @draft

# decisions

## open
- token-efficient agent usage uses generic CRUD commands plus short aliases instead of type-specific task or calendar subcommands @draft
- the Rust SQLite crate and async model are chosen based on simple CLI correctness, migration support, and testability rather than background service throughput @draft

# hooks
- Hooks run only after the triggering Store mutation succeeds and commits to the Store @draft
- Hook Query conditions use the same boolean field filter language as agent-store find @draft
- create, set, and unset Hooks evaluate their Query against the Record after the change; rm Hooks evaluate against the pre-delete Record snapshot @draft
- Hook Bash commands receive the affected Record snapshot on stdin in the default record output format @draft
- Hook command failures are reported to the caller without silently hiding the failed command, exit status, or captured stderr summary @draft
- Hooks run sequentially after the triggering mutation commits, from the project root, with a 30 second default timeout @draft
- Hook Bash commands receive AGENT_STORE_EVENT, AGENT_STORE_ID, AGENT_STORE_KIND, and AGENT_STORE_REL when applicable @draft
- a Hook timeout or non-zero exit makes the triggering CLI command exit non-zero after reporting that the Store mutation already committed @draft
- Hook stdout and stderr capture are capped at 8192 bytes each and the cap values are documented in command help @draft
- link and unlink Hooks evaluate their Query against the source Record and expose the relation and target Record ID through environment variables @draft
- Hook Bash commands receive AGENT_STORE_TARGET_ID for link and unlink events @draft

# context
- Quick Context output includes total Record count, counts by kind, Hook count, and the most recent Store activity timestamp when available @draft
- Quick Context output lists common Field names separately for each Record kind rather than as one global field list @draft
- Quick Context output summarizes common per-kind status values and date windows when fields such as status, due, or start exist @draft
- Quick Context output remains bounded by a documented byte limit regardless of Store size @draft
- agent-store ctx exits successfully for an initialized empty Store and prints zero counts instead of an error @draft
- Quick Context output includes Link count and relation-name counts when Links exist @draft

# query
- Query syntax supports and, or, not, parentheses, and comparison operators =, !=, <, <=, >, and >= @draft
- Query parsing treats multiple unquoted query arguments the same as one quoted query string @draft
- Query evaluation uses parsed Field types so date, timestamp, number, boolean, null, and text comparisons behave by value rather than raw string order @draft

# fields
- Field values preserve their raw input and are parsed in specificity order as null, boolean, date or timestamp, number, then text @draft
- key= stores an empty string Field value, key=null stores a null Field value, and agent-store unset removes a Field entirely @draft

# ids
- Record IDs are generated as 6-8 character random hash strings and creation retries when a generated ID already exists @draft
- Commands that accept a Record ID require an unambiguous existing short ID and report not-found errors without creating records implicitly @draft
